# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Foundry portal (apps/portal-web) — Vite env template
# Copy to `apps/portal-web/.env` for local dev. All vars are optional: sensible
# defaults are baked into the code so the portal runs with no .env at all.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# API base the SPA calls. Defaults to the relative "/api" (proxied to the
# Foundry server on :4000 by vite.config.ts). Set an absolute URL to bypass.
# VITE_API_BASE=/api

# --- Dogfood OAuth (M2) ------------------------------------------------------
# OFF by default: the everyday dev loop (API with AUTH_DISABLED=true, no IdP
# running) is unchanged. Set to `true` to arm the auth-code + PKCE flow against
# a locally-running IdP (the OAuth blueprint) — pair with AUTH_DISABLED=false on
# the Foundry API. The gen:oauth harness runs the IdP and seeds this client.
# VITE_OAUTH_ENABLED=true

# IdP base URL (where the generated OAuth server listens). Consumed by
# vite.config.ts as the proxy target for `/oauth/*` — the SPA calls those paths
# same-origin so the browser never makes a cross-origin request to the IdP (the
# generated server enables no CORS). The gen:oauth harness runs the IdP on :3000.
# VITE_OAUTH_ISSUER=http://localhost:3000

# OAuth client id the IdP seeds for the portal (SEED_CLIENT_ID in the harness).
# VITE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=foundry-portal

# Where the IdP redirects back after authorization. Must be a registered
# redirect_uri on the seeded client. The Vite dev origin + /callback.
# VITE_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/callback
